                            "year": 2012
                        },
                        "end": {
                            "month": 5,
                            "day": null,
                            "year": 2017
                        }
                    },
                    "company": "Shell",
                    "description": "* Modeled and applied advanced GIS and Remote Sensing techniques for energy and engineering projects: baseline and survey planning support with the use of desktop, web and mobile GIS, license/ area definitions and geodetic support according to OGP standardization, Hazard Identification and Risk Assessments (HIRA), Environmental Impact Assessments (EIA), seismic operations planning with concurrent use of real time field collected data, Emergency Response Planning in offline mode with the latest ESRI products.\n\n* Set up and deployed a variety of tools using the Enterprise Portal WebApp Builder forming prototype solutions towards zero incident culture and being adopted by gobal Operations teams. Among others, an Operations\u2019 Dashboard providing real-time vessel information, HSSE scorecards and survey status for offshore operations and a soil Profiler that allowed onshore seismic surveying staff to perform quick relief planning on the seismic operations terrain.\n\n* Designed and deployed a semi- automated (Model-Builder - based) well site selection workflow to serve well site planning under the continuously changing surface and sub-surface requirements of the oil and gas projects. The workflow allows for 60% time saving whenever technical or non-technical constraint updates are faced.\n\n*Implemented efficient and cost effective database and information management: database design, data modeling, and wed service set up. Her latest work on a stakeholder engagement database increased the efficiency of social sentiment recording for at least 20% and allowed for complex visualizations and application of business analytics.\n\n* Completed the automation and migration of existing geo-data workflows to the data center in India, succeeding a short term cost decrease of at least 30% and managing a very competitive contract and pricing for the future work.",
                    "title": "Geospatial Analyst",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
